{{Quote|Groups like the Happy Blasters give this trade a bad name. Almost anyone can tell you about the disasters these types of mercenaries have caused, incidents like the Benkal Plagues or the water crisis on Orroman, but not many people can remember the name of the scout who discovered their world or who charted the territory they live in.|Personal addendum in Korren Starchaser's datafiles|<ref name="Journal13">{{JournalCite|13|Scouts' Dispatch}}</ref>}}
The '''Benkal Plagues''' were a series of widely-known [[Disease/Legends|disease]] outbreaks that occurred at some point by the time of the existence of the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]]<ref name="Journal13" /> and originated in<ref name="Planetnamia">{{Planetnamia|other=the Benkal Plagues|system=[[Benkal system/Legends|Benkal system]]|legends=1}}</ref> the [[Benkal system/Legends|Benkal system]] of [[Wild Space/Legends|Wild Space]].<ref name="EAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}}</ref> The outbreaks were caused by a group of [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]] which, in a personal addendum to his [[Datafile/Legends|datafiles]], the New Republic [[Scout/Legends|scout]] [[Korren Starchaser]] compared to the ultra-violent [[Happy Blasters]] mercenary team.<ref name="Journal13" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Benkal Plagues were mentioned in "[[Scouts' Dispatch]]," a feature written by [[Peter Woodworth]] and published in the [[May]] [[1997]] [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 13|thirteenth issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]'' magazine.<ref name="Journal13" />

